OK, seriously—what are the best things that anyone has done to raise the social status of the scientists who helped create the covid vaccines?

Awards, honors, prizes, gifts, formal banquets… even just nice news features? Send me examples, I will compile a list.

For all positions, I submitted a cover letter and research statement. All psychology departments requested a teaching statement and most requested a diversity statement. I gave 3 job talks. I also prepped several versions of startup requests. (6/23)

Why is it so hard to find out how expensive scientific equipment is? At least ball park.

Timeline.  I submitted my first application in 8/2020 and accepted a job offer in 2/2021. I was not geographically restricted w/in North America so applied to positions anywhere in the US and Canada.  (5/23)
@Popher This is for real such a pain. Especially if you’re trying to build a start up request 😬

#LinkedIn may not be the best for work + social anymore, but it still remains the best tool for enterprise sales in tech #startups, if you're using it right!

Here's how:
- Add a note before sending a request, make it clear what you do, how you can help, and your ask.
